title: Unit 1: Introduction to Chemistry
description: Covers the scientific method, branches of chemistry, significant figures, dimensional analysis, and laboratory safety protocols.

title: Unit 2: Atomic Theory and Structure
description: Includes early atomic models (Dalton, Rutherford), subatomic particles, isotopes, atomic mass calculations, and the Bohr model.

title: Unit 3: Electronic Structure of Atoms
description: Focuses on quantum numbers, electron configurations, orbital diagrams, the Aufbau principle, Pauli exclusion, and Hund's rule.

title: Unit 4: Periodic Table and Properties
description: Covers periodic trends including atomic radii, ionization energy, electron affinity, electronegativity, and block classifications.
